# Livewire — class-based components

Project default is configured in `config/livewire.php` (`make_command.type` => `class`, `class_namespace` => `App\Livewire`, `class_path`, `view_path`).

## Required for new work

- **Always** create **class-based** Livewire components (dedicated PHP class + Blade view).
- Generate with Sail:
  ```bash
  ./vendor/bin/sail artisan make:livewire Path/ComponentName
  ```
  (`--type=class` is the default; do not pass `sfc` or `mfc`.)
- **Class:** `app/Livewire/{Path}/{ComponentName}.php` (`App\Livewire\...` namespace).
- **View:** `resources/views/livewire/{path}/{component-name}.blade.php` (kebab-case file name).
- Put markup and Flux UI in the Blade view; keep properties, validation, and actions in the PHP class.
- Prefer Pest tests targeting the component class (e.g. `Livewire::test(Index::class)`).

## Do not use for new components

- **Single-file components (SFC):** `resources/views/pages/**/⚡*.blade.php` with anonymous `class extends Component` in Blade.
- **Multi-file view-only components (MFC)** without a class under `app/Livewire/`.
- Creating new `⚡` prefixed page files for interactive Livewire UI.

## Routing

- Full pages: register the component class, for example:
  ```php
  Route::livewire('leads', \App\Livewire\Leads\Index::class)->name('leads.index');
  ```
  or `Route::get('leads', \App\Livewire\Leads\Index::class)` when appropriate.
- Do **not** add new `Route::livewire(..., 'pages::...')` entries for new CRM/features; use the class FQCN instead.

## Legacy (existing code)

- All Livewire components use class-based structure under `app/Livewire/` with views in `resources/views/livewire/`.
- Do not reintroduce SFC (`⚡*.blade.php`) or MFC-only components.

